Two weeks after the launching of 4G+, which offers customers faster data speeds, MTN Nigeria has introduced a price slash across all its data plans and offerings. Under the new price structure, customers will enjoy more value for their money with up to 30% more data volume for 30-day plans. They will also enjoy up to 100% incremental volume for weekly data plans and 25percent incremental volume for daily plans. Also, new customers will enjoy introductory offers, with access to prices as low as N50 for 50MB, N500 for 2GB as well as receive a 100percent bonus on data purchases for four months. Commenting on the new price structure, the Chief marketing officer, Rahul Desaid, said that the data price slash could not have come at a better time for customers with the faster internet speeds delivered by the launch of 4G+. “We have seen that faster data speed means more data usage,” he said. JUST IN: MTN launches 4G+ in Lagos, Abuja, Port-Harcourt NCC: We’re still not satisfied with service quality across networks 9mobile excites customers with new MiFi offer Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin